  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        Consider the basis <m>\basis{B} = \bopen\ve{v}_1,\ve{v}_2\bclose</m> of <m>\reals^2</m>, where <m>\ve{v}_1 = \begin{bmatrix} 1\\0 \end{bmatrix}</m> and <m>\ve{v}_2 = \begin{bmatrix} 1\\1 \end{bmatrix}</m>, and let <m>T:\reals^2\to \reals^2</m> be the linear transformation satisfying
        <me>
